China focus: China pledges to minimize impact of river pollution on Russia 

By Tian Sulei, Wang Jingzhong and Wang Jiangang 

BEIJING, Nov. 24 (Xinhua) -- China pledged on Thursday it will  try its utmost to minimize the impact of northeast China's Songhua River pollution on the neighboring Russia, including intensifying  monitoring and water quality control measures.
Water supply in Harbin, capital of  northeast China's Heilongjiang Province, which is now under a  four-day water cutoff, will be resumed at 11 p.m. on Sunday as  scheduled, Du Yuxin, secretary of Harbin City Committee of the  Communist Party of China (CPC) said.
